<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.D0.94.D0.B8.D0.BB.D0.BE.D0.B2"><a href="/w/index.php?title=%D0%9B%D1%8E%D0%B1%D0%B5%D0%BD_%D0%94%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Любен Дилов (page does not exist)">Дилов, Любен</a>. <i>Пътят на Икар</i>. Захари Стоянов. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9547393383" class="internal">ISBN 954-739-338-3</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%D0%9F%D1%8A%D1%82%D1%8F%D1%82+%D0%BD%D0%B0+%D0%98%D0%BA%D0%B0%D1%80&amp;rft.aulast=%D0%94%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2&amp;rft.aufirst=%D0%9B%D1%8E%D0%B1%D0%B5%D0%BD&amp;rft.au=%D0%94%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%BE%D0%B2%2C+%D0%9B%D1%8E%D0%B1%D0%B5%D0%BD&amp;rft.pub=%D0%97%D0%B0%D1%85%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B8+%D0%A1%D1%82%D0%BE%D1%8F%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%B2&amp;rft.isbn=954-739-338-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREF.D0.9A.D0.B5.D1.81.D0.B0.D1.80.D0.BE.D0.B2.D1.81.D0.BA.D0.B81983"><a href="/w/index.php?title=%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B0_%D0%9A%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Никола Кесаровски (page does not exist)">Кесаровски, Никола</a> (1983). <i>Петият закон</i>. Отечество.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%D0%9F%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82+%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BD&amp;rft.aulast=%D0%9A%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8&amp;rft.aufirst=%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B0&amp;rft.au=%D0%9A%D0%B5%D1%81%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%2C+%D0%9D%D0%B8%D0%BA%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B0&amp;rft.date=1983&amp;rft.pub=%D0%9E%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%87%D0%B5%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B2%D0%BE&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFAsimovStanley_Asimov1995">Asimov, Isaac; Stanley Asimov (1995). <i>Yours, Isaac Asimov: A Life in Letters</i>. Doubleday. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0385476221" class="internal">ISBN 0-385-47622-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Yours%2C+Isaac+Asimov%3A+A+Life+in+Letters&amp;rft.aulast=Asimov&amp;rft.aufirst=Isaac&amp;rft.au=Asimov%2C+Isaac&amp;rft.au=Stanley+Asimov&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Doubleday&amp;rft.isbn=0-385-47622-1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFEllison1994">Ellison, Harlan (1994). <i>I, Robot: The illustrated screenplay</i>. Aspect. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0446670626" class="internal">ISBN 0-446-67062-6</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=I%2C+Robot%3A+The+illustrated+screenplay&amp;rft.aulast=Ellison&amp;rft.aufirst=Harlan&amp;rft.au=Ellison%2C+Harlan&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.pub=Aspect&amp;rft.isbn=0-446-67062-6&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> "Suggested by" Isaac Asimov's robot stories—two stops removed from "based on" and "inspired by", the credit implies something scribbled on a bar napkin—<a href="/wiki/Alex_Proyas" title="Alex Proyas">Alex Proyas</a>' science-fiction thriller <i>I, Robot</i> sprinkles Asimov's ideas like seasoning on a giant bucket of popcorn. [...] Asimov's simple and seemingly foolproof Laws of Robotics, designed to protect human beings and robots alike from harm, are subject to loopholes that the author loved to exploit. After all, much of humanity agrees in principle to abide by the <a href="/wiki/Ten_Commandments" title="Ten Commandments">Ten Commandments</a>, but <a href="/wiki/Free_will" title="Free will">free will</a>, circumstance, and contradictory impulses can find wiggle room in even the most unambiguous decree. Whenever <i>I, Robot</i> pauses between action beats, Proyas captures some of the excitement of movies like <i><a href="/wiki/The_Matrix" title="The Matrix">The Matrix</a>,</i> <i><a href="/wiki/Minority_Report_(film)" title="Minority Report (film)">Minority Report</a></i>, and <i><a href="/wiki/A.I._(film)" title="A.I. (film)" class="mw-redirect">A.I.</a></i>, all of which proved that philosophy and social commentary could be smuggled into spectacle. Had the film been based on Asimov's stories, rather than merely "suggested by" them, Proyas might have achieved the intellectual heft missing from his stylish 1998 <a href="/wiki/Cult_film" title="Cult film">cult</a> favorite <i><a href="/wiki/Dark_City_(1998_film)" title="Dark City (1998 film)">Dark City</a>.</i> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFTobias2004">Tobias, Scott (20 July 2004). <a href="http://avclub.com/content/node/17881" class="external text" title="http://avclub.com/content/node/17881" rel="nofollow">"review of I, Robot"</a>. <a href="/wiki/The_Onion" title="The Onion">The Onion A.V. Club</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://avclub.com/content/node/17881" class="external free" title="http://avclub.com/content/node/17881" rel="nofollow">http://avclub.com/content/node/17881</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-06-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=review+of+I%2C+Robot&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Tobias&amp;rft.aufirst=Scott&amp;rft.au=Tobias%2C+Scott&amp;rft.date=20+July+2004&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BThe+Onion%7CThe+Onion+A.V.+Club%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Favclub.com%2Fcontent%2Fnode%2F17881&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-moravec-29">^ <a href="#cite_ref-moravec_29-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-moravec_29-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="/wiki/Hans_Moravec" title="Hans Moravec">Moravec, Hans</a>. "The Age of Robots", <i>Extro 1, Proceedings of the First <a href="/wiki/Extropy_Institute" title="Extropy Institute" class="mw-redirect">Extropy Institute</a> Conference on TransHumanist Thought</i> (1994) pp. 84–100. <a href="http://www.frc.ri.cmu.edu/~hpm/project.archive/general.articles/1993/Robot93.html" class="external text" title="http://www.frc.ri.cmu.edu/~hpm/project.archive/general.articles/1993/Robot93.html" rel="nofollow">June 1993 version</a> available online.</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="">"<a href="http://www.newscientist.com/channel/mech-tech/robots/mg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html" class="external text" title="http://www.newscientist.com/channel/mech-tech/robots/mg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html" rel="nofollow">Rules for the modern robot</a>". <i>New Scientist</i> (2544): 27. 27 March 2006<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.newscientist.com/channel/mech-tech/robots/mg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html" class="external free" title="http://www.newscientist.com/channel/mech-tech/robots/mg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.newscientist.com/channel/mech-tech/robots/mg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-06-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Rules+for+the+modern+robot&amp;rft.jtitle=New+Scientist&amp;rft.date=27+March+2006&amp;rft.issue=2544&amp;rft.pages=27&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Fchannel%2Fmech-tech%2Frobots%2Fmg18925445.600-rules-for-the-modern-robot.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFSawyer1991">Sawyer, Robert J. (1991). <a href="http://www.sfwriter.com/rmasilaw.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sfwriter.com/rmasilaw.htm" rel="nofollow">"On Asimov's Three Laws of Robotics"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.sfwriter.com/rmasilaw.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.sfwriter.com/rmasilaw.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.sfwriter.com/rmasilaw.htm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2006-06-12</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=On+Asimov%27s+Three+Laws+of+Robotics&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Sawyer&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert+J.&amp;rft.au=Sawyer%2C+Robert+J.&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sfwriter.com%2Frmasilaw.htm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> Clarke, Roger. <i>Asimov's laws of robotics: Implications for information technology</i>. <a href="http://csdl.computer.org/comp/mags/co/1993/12/rz053abs.htm" class="external text" title="http://csdl.computer.org/comp/mags/co/1993/12/rz053abs.htm" rel="nofollow">Part 1: IEEE Computer, December 1993, p53–61.</a> <a href="http://csdl.computer.org/comp/mags/co/1994/01/r1057abs.htm" class="external text" title="http://csdl.computer.org/comp/mags/co/1994/01/r1057abs.htm" rel="nofollow">Part 2: IEEE Computer, Jan 1994, p57–66.</a> Both parts are available without fee at <a href="http://www.anu.edu.au/people/Roger.Clarke/SOS/Asimov.html" class="external text" title="http://www.anu.edu.au/people/Roger.Clarke/SOS/Asimov.html" rel="nofollow">Australian National University</a>. Under "Enhancements to codes of ethics".</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news"><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/6425927.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/6425927.stm" rel="nofollow">"Robotic age poses ethical dilemma"</a>. <a href="/wiki/BBC_News" title="BBC News">BBC News</a>. <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-03-07"><a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a>-<a href="/wiki/March_7" title="March 7">03-07</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/6425927.stm" class="external free" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/6425927.stm" rel="nofollow">http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/6425927.stm</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-03-07</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Robotic+age+poses+ethical+dilemma&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2007-03-07%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BBBC+News%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Ftechnology%2F6425927.stm&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Three_Laws_of_Robotics"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
